723639f-a.title: Manhattan: Union Square (West) - 15th Street (East) - [Union Square Park.]
723639f-a.text:
Union Square West, north from East 15th Street, showing
removal of the 8roadway streetoar tracks by the Works Progress
Administration. Union Square Park is to the right extending
to 17th Street. Above that point this thoroughfare regains
its proper identity. The white building at the N. E. corner
there is occupied by Butler Brothers. Cverhead appears the
Metropolitan Life Insurance Co. tower.
View 2 is photographed from 16th Street while No. 3 is
oloser to 17th Street, the three collectively being progress-
ive.
June 10, 1937
Views 1,2,3
Works Progress Administration
Five Boroughs Project
CREDIT LINE IMPERATIVE

723651f-b.title: Manhattan: Union Square (West) - 15th Street - Broadway.
723651f-b.text:
(1)
Union Square West, north from and including the S.W. corner of
15th Street, to and including Broadway. Also shown is 17th Street
(east), south from and including Broadway, to but not including
Fourth Ave.
June 2, 1904.
Brown Brothers.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, showing open street cars on the Broadway Line.
About 1904.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

723649f-b.title: Manhattan: Union Square (West) - 15th Street.
723649f-b.text:
(1)
Union Sguare West, north from but not including 15th Street.
Also shown is 16th Street, north side, west from and including Dnion
Square West, and Broadway, west side, north from and including 17th
Street, to and including 18th Street.
October 30, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
ND REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same view, at a later date, showing part of the Park completed,
taken from the New York Edison Building at No. 4 Irving Place.
September 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
